<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>When bundles overlap it may make sense to merge them into one bundle with one Bundle record.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>Each Match record has a bundleID field added to it to point to its corresponding Bundle record.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>One complication is that adding records may cause bundles to merge if the new record causes one bundle to overlap another.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>It is easy to compute the aggregate statistics for the bundle table once each match record has an assigned bundle ID.</a>
<a name="4">[4]</a> <a href="#4" id=4>These new records may create new bundles or may add to an existing bundle.</a>
<a name="5">[5]</a> <a href="#5" id=5>This suggests creating a Bundle table that records these statistics.</a>
</body>
